Elements that are Not Semantic

Naughty HTML tags who previously used to define styling-type behaviour, instead of leaving to CSS as God intended have been deprecated and if you use them, people will laught at you.
Center

I'm sad to see center go, personally. Always made me feel I was getting somewhere when I centered a few things.

But, of course, //where// the elements go isn't any business of HTML - how do you put the element "in the center" if someone's listening to your page?
farewell, center.
